However, a more modern approach would be to use the `height` and `width` properties with `vh` (viewport height) and `vw` (viewport width) units:

```css
body {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  background-color: #e8e8e8;
  font-family: 'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  text-align: center;
  /* Add these lines */
  height: 100vh;
  width: 100vw;
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

Or even simpler, just ensure that the `html` element also has no margins or paddings:

```css
html, body {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  height: 100%;
  width: 100%;
}

body {
  background-color: #e8e8e8;
  font-family: 'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  text-align: center;
}
```

Any of these approaches will ensure that the background color covers the entire page without any margins or paddings.

